info.abstract:
[Behaviour]
Compute the IFI fire danger index. Input measure is expected to follow the format:
- the time series is expressed in days;
- for each day there must be a group of 8 ordered values: radiation_mean (W m-2),radiation_max (W m-2),temperature_mean (C),
temperature_max (C),total_precipitation (mm),wind_speed_mean (km h-1),relative_humidity_mean (%),relative_humidity_min (%);
- all inputs must be of the same oph_type.

[Parameters]
- input measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- output measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- measure : input measures.
- index : name of the requested index.
					'DC' : drought code;
					'MC' : meteorological code;
					'R' : R coefficient;
					'FC' : fuel code;
					'IFI' : integrated fire danger index (default).

[Return type]
Binary-array.

[Examples]
Compute the IFI index from oph_doubles.
oph_fdi_ifi('OPH_DOUBLE','OPH_DOUBLE',measure)
